
rosprolog is a wrapper around swi-prolog that uses an additional user-init file.
Some new predicates are added in this file:
 * register_ros_package( <ros-package-name> )
   Loads the initialization file from $(rospack find <ros-package-name>)/prolog/<prolog-file-path>.
 * use_ros_module( <ros-package-name>, '<prolog-file-path>' )
   Load a prolog module from $(rospack find <ros-package-name>)/prolog/<prolog-file-path>.
 * ros_package_path( Package, Path )
   Get the absolute path of a package.
 * ros_info( Msg ), ros_warning( Msg ), ros_error( Msg )
   Send logging messages to ROS master.
 * tf_lookup_transform( Target, Source, Transform ), ...
   TFTransformListener interface.

To run rosprolog, use:
rosrun rosprolog rosprolog

To start a prolog package within rosprolog (incl. calling its init.pl file and all init.pl of referenced packages), use:
rosrun rosprolog rosprolog <pkgname>

